{
  "stem": "12494.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so that's where we-- that's where we wound up.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We went home for-- I went home in the summer of '39, in the [INAUDIBLE], in May or so of 1939, to make my annual examination so that I would be officially qualified to go to the next grade.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But otherwise we were, from July '38 to September '39.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My brother and I were in-- in [NON-ENGLISH], French part of Switzerland at the [?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Institut ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Ascher, ?] where we learned French and became fluent in French.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And had a very good time.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, first was the-- first they sent us because they were worried about the Czechoslovakian crisis in the summer of 1938.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then, as the Czechoslovakian crisis didn't settle, they left us there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then, after the Czechoslovakian crisis settled, it became very clear that things are not really settled because only part of Czechoslovakia was absorbed by Germany, but there was a danger that the rest would be absorbed.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my parents said, why don't you stay some longer?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then, of course, came March, 1939, when the rest of Czechoslovakia was absorbed by Germany.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "After that there was a small pause.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They asked me to go home and to make my examination for the year.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And as soon as I made my examination, my parents decided that the Polish crisis was pretty bad, so they sent us back to Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then you may be-- you may ask the question as to, well, why didn't we stay in Switzerland during the war?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Well, that was very simple because my dad, who-- and I say this seriously-- he was really a leader of men and a very thoughtful individual and very influential individual.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
